title: Aesop's Fables, Volume 2 (Fables 26-50)
creator: Aesop
description: Librivox recording of Aesop's Fables, Volume 2 (Fables 26-50). Dating back to the 6th century BC, Aesop's Fables tell universal truths through the use of simple allegories that are easily understood. Though almost nothing is known of Aesop himself, and some scholars question whether he existed at all, these stories stand as timeless classics known in almost every culture in the world. This is volume 2 of 12. (Summary by Chip) Read by: Fables 1-2: Kristin Luoma Fables 3-5: Annie Coleman Fables 6-9: ajfluke Fables 10-12: Desdemona Fables 13-15: Basil Munroe Godevenos Fables 16-18: phoenixascending Fable 19: Rainer Fable 20: Patrick McNeal Fables 21-22: Sara Schein Fable 23: Gesine Fable 24: Patrick McNeal Fable 25: Robert Garrison For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.
